1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,580
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:37,979
Episode 25

3
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,509
My father told me about Peking, the Forbidden City

4
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:43,039
and the like when I was young.

5
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:45,080
So, I expected to perform in Peking

6
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:46,440
when I grew up.

7
00:01:46,910 --> 00:01:48,310
People move up the ladder.

8
00:01:48,910 --> 00:01:50,680
I was very happy when I left Pingyang.

9
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:57,000
You are no ordinary man as well.

10
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:00,120
Wait a second here.

11
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:02,270
I’m going to make tea. Please.

12
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:12,360
Cheng.

13
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,270
Qi’s Mansion

14
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:15,830
is quite interesting.

15
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:17,720
No flowers, no trees.

16
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,030
A vegetable garden is here.

17
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,270
Look at the radish.

18
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:24,160
Do you recognize radish?

19
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,079
I thought it is artemisia.

20
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,880
It’s radish.

21
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,079
Impressive, Mr. Shang.

22
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,750
Awesome.

23
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,240
I’m not.

24
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:40,000
You were born with a silver spoon

25
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,190
in your mouth.

26
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:42,520
Let me tell you.

27
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,360
If you end up in the wild one day

28
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,670
and know which plant is editable

29
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:46,670
and which isn’t,

30
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,750
it’s much important than treasures and antiques

31
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,829
you know.

32
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,470
What are you thinking about?

33
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,470
How can I end up in the wild?

34
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,390
That’s possible.

35
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,030
Considering the current situation,

36
00:02:58,670 --> 00:02:59,880
a war could be started.

37
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,240
If a war is truly started,

38
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:04,440
even the aristocratic families of generations

39
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,440
will come to naught.

40
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:08,440
The nobles

41
00:03:09,110 --> 00:03:11,550
from influential family may die beside the road.

42
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:15,600
Growing crops to feed myself is better.

43
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:18,160
Sir. You’re a gardener

44
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,000
and you know a war is coming.

45
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,720
The rich people

46
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,390
could have hidden away.

47
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:25,110
It’s not miserable as you said.

48
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,190
This war is different from the previous ones.

49
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,880
Maybe the whole world is going to get involved.

50
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:31,670
Where

51
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,000
can you run away?

52
00:03:33,390 --> 00:03:34,960
You can’t run to the moon, can you?

53
00:03:35,270 --> 00:03:36,600
The whole world?

54
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:38,079
Isn’t it crazy?

55
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,520
Crazy people are full of the world.

56
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:42,600
The weapons nowadays

57
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,750
are much better than before.

58
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,960
In the ancient times,

59
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,440
cavalrymen and bows are powerful the most.

60
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,360
But now

61
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,240
there are airplanes and cannons.

62
00:03:55,670 --> 00:03:57,390
The triggers of guns pulled,

63
00:03:57,390 --> 00:03:58,240
people

64
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,630
will fall like mowing wheat.

65
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,470
If the world is at war,

66
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:05,630
where should I perform?

67
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,750
The whole world is at war

68
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,190
and you still think about performing?

69
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,110
You’re crazy too.

70
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:12,880
Alright.

71
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:15,080
Not that miserable.

72
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,440
Dynasties changed many times,

73
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:20,350
but the song and dance were performed as ever.

74
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:23,230
Amusement is the nature of humankind

75
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,510
like the war.

76
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:25,920
It’s inseparable.

77
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:28,000
That’s why a celebration banquet is always held

78
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,480
after a war.

79
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,040
Anyway,

80
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:33,320
businessmen like me are unlucky.

81
00:04:33,670 --> 00:04:34,760
Once the war is started,

82
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,640
all my business will be ruined.

83
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,270
The wealth will also be coveted by the military.

84
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,390
All the money we earn

85
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,790
will be used for military purposes.

86
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:45,880
At that time,

87
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,920
you’ll have to live on the money of Shuiyun.

88
00:04:49,070 --> 00:04:49,790
Yes, right.

89
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:51,200
By that time,

90
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:56,110
Mr. Shang, please offer me alms.

91
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:59,600
I’ve never seen anyone

92
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,920
relies on a performer like you.

93
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:02,790
Sir.

94
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:04,600
You can also rely on us.

95
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,670
We have many young performers in Shuiyun.

96
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:08,070
You can support one of them now

97
00:05:08,070 --> 00:05:09,480
and let them feed you at that time.

98
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:14,390
Don’t be fooled by him.

99
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:16,600
He always teases people like this.

100
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:18,510
He feels happy

101
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,640
when guests are surprised.

102
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:22,510
Jiulang.

103
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:24,720
This is...

104
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:28,790
Xirui, it's been a while.

105
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,160
Lord Qi!

106
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,440
Xirui.

107
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:53,110
Was the Tale of Dragon

108
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,670
performed by you?

109
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,230
Yes.

110
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,670
It’s not good. Please give me advices.

111
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,600
Not good indeed.

112
00:06:02,510 --> 00:06:03,390
First of all,

113
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:07,320
the etiquette, wording, and costumes

114
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:09,720
are wrong.

115
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,720
Not to mention Empress Dowager

116
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,790
didn’t like osmanthus wine at all.

117
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,790
Your line:

118
00:06:16,790 --> 00:06:19,000
Drink osmanthus wine together when free.

119
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:21,070
Isn’t it nonsense?

120
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:23,790
You’re right, lord.

121
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:24,760
But no one

122
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:26,200
told me this.

123
00:06:26,350 --> 00:06:27,720
You can look it up

124
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,390
or ask others.

125
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:33,600
Not all old men from the palace are dead.

126
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,670
You made this up

127
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:37,480
as you please.

128
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:40,640
What if people

129
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,920
believe it?

130
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,110
You're right.

131
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,790
I’ll change it once I get back.

132
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:50,440
You’re bullying Xirui.

133
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,640
Ignore him.

134
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:56,070
Who was the guy

135
00:06:57,510 --> 00:06:58,720
crying

136
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:02,070
when he watched the show that day?

137
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:05,480
Why do you help an outsider?

138
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:09,510
Xirui.

139
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:11,950
It’s been many years since we met.

140
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:13,790
Your performance

141
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:16,270
made a big progress.

142
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:19,920
Niulang, did you go to my show as well?

143
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,160
He did

144
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,550
and also gave you many presents.

145
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:26,440
You come to me today.

146
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,040
You are not here

147
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:31,110
to have tea with me,

148
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:34,600
are you?

149
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:44,110
Well... Well...

150
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:46,200
Mr. Shang is still like a child.

151
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,390
He’s too nervous to speak when he sees you.

152
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,480
Well,

153
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,790
let me tell you.

154
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,480
We want to

155
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:57,270
invite Mr. Ning to perform with Mr. Shang.

156
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:02,300
(Invitation)

157
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:05,100
(Invite Mr. Ning Jiulang to the farewell banquet
for Commissioner Liu Hanyun)

158
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,820
(Invitation)

159
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,720
I know

160
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,550
Liu Hanyun.

161
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:29,110
I never thought he’d be a high-ranking official

162
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:32,280
in the new government.

163
00:08:32,909 --> 00:08:34,280
Jiulang, you know him?

164
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,150
It’s been decades.

165
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:40,200
I can’t believe

166
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,760
he changed his name back.

167
00:08:45,110 --> 00:08:46,200
How so?

168
00:08:46,710 --> 00:08:48,910
He was unlucky when he went into the palace.

169
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:53,400
Empress Dowager didn’t get along well with Li Hongzhang,

170
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:56,470
unwilling to recruit people of Han nationality as officials.

171
00:08:56,710 --> 00:08:59,230
So, the character Han in his name

172
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:00,640
was marked,

173
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:03,320
and he’d be driven out of the palace.

174
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,080
Before we performed,

175
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:08,280
I told Empress Dowager

176
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:10,590
his name was Liu Jinyun.

177
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:14,280
I also bribed the eunuch to lie for us.

178
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:16,150
Finally,

179
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,400
he got it over.

180
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:22,000
There’s such a story between you.

181
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:24,910
Liu Hanyun.

182
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,400
I don’t like him.

183
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:30,400
His Majesty was kind to him.

184
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,230
The feudal dynasty collapsed

185
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:35,910
and he surrendered to Kuomintang immediately.

186
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:37,910
That’s apostasy.

187
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:44,910
How could you take him as your godfather?

188
00:09:45,470 --> 00:09:47,030
I’m a better choice than him.

189
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,280
Jiulang.

190
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,110
Don’t perform for him.

191
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,000
That’s a shame.

192
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,880
Besides,

193
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,110
Jiulang and you are not related.

194
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:09,080
Now that he has retired,

195
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,230
he won’t perform anymore.

196
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,960
Why should he break the rule for you?

197
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,520
You’re right, Lord.

198
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,590
We’re leaving.

199
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:26,320
They have connections.

200
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,030
Mr. Shang

201
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:31,550
is Niu Jiulang’s favorite apprentice.

202
00:10:31,550 --> 00:10:32,440
What are you talking about?

203
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,910
If master and apprentice perform together,

204
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,840
the show would be a hit.

205
00:10:36,110 --> 00:10:36,960
Who said that?

206
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,320
Who told you I was his apprentice?

207
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,910
At the moment.

208
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,790
Jiulang.

209
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,550
You always say your life is perfect.

210
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,110
The only regret

211
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:55,760
is that you don’t have a good apprentice

212
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:56,840
to take up your mantle.

213
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,710
Xirui is waiting.

214
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,710
Why not agree?

215
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:13,000
Go ahead.

216
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,880
Kneel and call master.

217
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:15,790
On your knees.

218
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:16,280
Wait.

219
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:22,590
I've said this before.

220
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:25,520
I only taught you operas,

221
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,400
but wouldn’t take you as apprentice.

222
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,110
You...

223
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:35,910
After all,

224
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:39,280
you’re my old friend.

225
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:41,960
I won't

226
00:11:43,590 --> 00:11:44,880
refuse

227
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:48,840
your invitation.

228
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,030
-What are you doing?
-You can’t get in!

229
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,440
-Make way for me!
-You can’t get in!

230
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,440
It's the backstage.

231
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,550
Mind your manners!

232
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:06,520
Ma’am.

233
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:07,400
You can’t get in.

234
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:11,910
I’m wondering why my husband

235
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:13,520
frequently

236
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,470
comes to the Opera Association.

237
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:20,150
So, a vixen is seducing him

238
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:21,640
here.

239
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:23,110
Come out!

240
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,000
Come out!

241
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:30,080
You feel ashamed now?

242
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:32,710
Why did you

243
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,590
seduce my husband then?

244
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,320
No wonder your parents drove you out of family

245
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,710
and didn’t allow you to use family surname.

246
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:39,760
Make way. Make way.

247
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,060
-Mr. Shang. It’s time for the show.
-I’m busy.

248
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,230
Get away.

249
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:44,150
-What are you doing?
-Get up.

250
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,670
What? Don’t you know it?

251
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,350
-You can’t get in.
-You can’t.

252
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:48,150
Make way.

253
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,840
Let me go.

254
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:51,110
-Get away.
-You can’t get in.

255
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:54,760
Don’t touch her! Don’t touch her!

256
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,910
Call Yuan Xiaodi here! Call Yuan Xiaodi here!

257
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:59,110
Got it.

258
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,200
-What are you doing? Let go.
-Let me go.

259
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,710
Go tell Mr. Cheng.

260
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,880
Let me go.

261
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,640
Alright.

262
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:07,030
Mr. Yuan is coming!

263
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,710
-Mr. Yuan. Look.
-Let me go.

264
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,790
Silent! Mr. Yuan comes!

265
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:12,710
Let me go.

266
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:26,880
Go home.

267
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,670
Let me go.

268
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:30,200
What?

269
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,790
You want to drive me away

270
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:35,670
and then marry her, right?

271
00:13:35,670 --> 00:13:36,520
What nonsense is that?

272
00:13:37,590 --> 00:13:38,760
It’s disgracing.

273
00:13:40,470 --> 00:13:42,030
Disgracing?

274
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:43,640
What did I say?

275
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,880
How did I disgrace you?

276
00:13:47,350 --> 00:13:49,880
I’m pregnant,

277
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:52,470
while you frequently go to the theater

278
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,470
and give her gifts.

279
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,640
Hold her hand.

280
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:58,320
Draw eyebrows face to face.

281
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,150
Do you know what people say about you?

282
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,000
You don’t behave like a master.

283
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:06,640
She doesn't behave like an apprentice.

284
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,710
I disgraced you?

285
00:14:08,710 --> 00:14:10,470
How did I disgrace you?

286
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:12,640
I knew Yu Qing before you.

287
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:14,550
We’d be together long ago if we could.

288
